<paragraph blockId="37.[189,1399,1852,2025]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[298,401,1852,1878]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">holotype</typeStatus>
female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunetti" authorityYear="1915" box="[527,958,1852,1878]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asciiformis" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[527,958,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) asciiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Darjeeling, 
<collectingCountry box="[1168,1231,1852,1878]" name="India" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">India</collectingCountry>
, is known. By the hyaline wing, oblique vein dm-cu and the short tergum II this species recalls 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shiraki" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[298,481,1925,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="farinosa" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[298,313,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[329,357,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis box="[364,481,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">) farinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[490,582,1925,1951]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[642,830,1925,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubicola" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[642,830,1925,1952]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">S. (A.) nubicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[839,934,1925,1951]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but differs by the entirely yellow pro- and mesolegs (in all others at least tarsomeres 4 and 5 of pro- and mesotarsus black) and by the entirely black abdomen.
</paragraph>
